description.narrative:
The project Increased availability and use of official statistics in North Macedonia, is about partnership cooperation between the Statistics Sweden and the State Statistical Office of North Macedonia. The overall project goal is to reach increased user confidence in North Macedonia, by the means of increased availability and use of official statistics in the country.  

To contribute to the achievement of the overall goal, the project will work towards the following outcomes: 
- improved efficiency of the statistical production process;
- increased range and improved quality of statistical production;
- improved internal and external communications;
- improved efficiency of human resource management.

The theory of change of the proposed intervention is as follows - IF the availability and use of official statistics in the country increases: (1) by increasing and further developing of the institutional capacity and knowledge at SSO and thereby by improving the efficiency of statistical production process; (2) as well as by increasing the range and improving the quality of statistical production; (3) by improving the communication of statistical data in the public; AND, IF SSO (4) improves efficiency of its human resource management; THEN SSO will contribute to increased users confidence in the accuracy and reliability of provided statistical data. This will enable the institutions to prepare their social policies, and the researchers and NGO's to utilize the data, and to argue for the rights of the poor. At the same time, SSO will comply to the existing EU requirements (2019 Communication on EU Enlargement Policy , North Macedonia 2019 Report - Chapter 18 and European Statistics Code of Practice) and the Agenda 2030 (SDG 5; SDG 16 and SDG 17).

The project budget is 14,000,000.00 SEK for the period September 2019 - June 2023.
